  "title": "RESIDENT ARCHITECT (RA)",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Resident Architect (RA)</strong></u></p><ul><li>Minimum 8 years of experience, of which at least 5 years in major construction works in buildings, architectural and fitting out works</li><li>Possess degree recognised by BOA</li><li>Must be a Singaporean / PR</li><li>Conversant with statutory code and requirements for site supervision, quality control procedures, construction administration and submission of progress report</li><li>Possess strong leadership skills</li><li>Familiar with all procedures in the Workplace Safety & Health Manual</li><li>Supervise all works to ensure that Contractor complies with all Contract/Authority/Agency requirements</li><li>Manage a team of Site Staff, and lead the supervision of architectural works</li><li>Review all drawings and specifications and highlight any discrepancies, non-workable and/or missing details to Architect</li><li>Review and comment on all construction method statements, risk assessments for works, workplans, Design for Safety (DfS) workshops and SOP proposals</li><li>Assist Architect with application for TOP and CSC</li><li>Monitor project progress to ensure timely completion and prepare necessary site progress and status report for update to Client</li><li>Adhere to regulations and requirements of all stakeholders for any supervision work, while ensuring proper supervision</li><li>Monitor contractors' safety performance, and participate actively in site safety management</li><li>Conduct roving safety inspections, emergency & incident response and facts finding</li><li>Report any accident/incident/near miss on site</li></ul><p>General Information:</p><ul><li>Location of site: Tampines, Singapore</li><li>Contract period: Now to June 2028, with option to extend</li><li>Salary: $8,000 to $9,000 monthly, depending on experience</li></ul>",
